list.description:
AmazonJoyo Co. Ltd Finance Operations department seeks a bright,
articulated and detail-oriented Japanese speaking Accounts Payable Financial
Analyst to play the important role in Japan Accounts Payable Financial
Operations Team (A/P) in Beijing, China. This position will work cross
functionally with Worldwide Shared Services, Retail Vendor Management, Retail
Finance, and Global Operations to support the team’s accounts payables
operations. This position will focus on Retail Inventory Payables with a strong
emphasis on paying vendors on time and all related activities in order to
achieve this mission such as problem resolving and handling inquires and
escalations. Furthermore, this position will also support process improvement,
controllership policies and procedures.          
                     
     
  
 
	Areas of Responsibilities includes but not limited to:  
• Investigate invoicing discrepancy and fix
problems in order to issue payments on time 
• Respond to vendors’ and internal inquiries with
focus on high customer satisfaction 
• Manage any systematic and operational issue
occurred during invoice processing 
• Analyze and report metrics to management 
• Support daily execution of various payments to
vendors globally 
• Research the reason of failed payments and
ensure timely and accurate payment reissuance 
• Participate in Operational Excellence activities
such as Kaizen/Green Belt 
 
Basic Qualifications: 
• Fluent in both written and spoken business
Japanese (passed N1 or Level 1 of Japanese Language Proficiency Test) and
English (TOEIC over 700) 
• Intermediate to advanced proficiency in
Microsoft Excel 
• Strong interpersonal written and oral
communication skills in a cross cultural setting with international counterparts 
• Internal and external customer focus and a work
ethic based on a strong desire to exceed expectations 
• Strong analytical skills including the ability
to deep dive while also seeing and understand the big picture 
• Demonstrated ability to meet deadlines while
supporting multiple competing priorities 
 
Preferred Qualifications: 
• B.S. or B.A. in Finance / Accounting or related
field is preferred 
• 0-3 years of relevant experience in Finance,
Accounts Payable, or a Process improvement role 
• Experience in creating/leading operational
process 
• Experience in resolving complex problems
cross-functionally 
• Experience in working closely with
vendors/customers 
• Experience with Oracle Financials is desired 
• Track record of dealing with ambiguity
list.name: 亚马逊中国招聘Financial Analyst, Japan Accounts Payable

list.description:
Account Executive – Field Sales in China
  
 
	Business job title: Account Executive – Field Sales
(including Associate and Senior)
  
 
	Purpose of Position:
  
 
	To develop new business as well as maintain and deepen
existing customer relationships through face-to-face sales call in order to
achieve personal sales targets and market goals within the small to large-sized
customer segment.
  
 
	Minimum Requirements：
  
 
	Education: Bachelor’s degree or equivalent
  
 
	Experience:No
work experience limited for Associate Account Executive – Field Sales;
  
 
	Two (2) years for Account Executive –
Field Sales and three (3) years for Senior, in commercial or industrial sales
  
 
	Proficiency in English & Simplified Chinese language
  
 
	Familiar
with Chinese culture and market environment
  
 
	Strong presentation skills
  
 
	Able
to influence and negotiate with others using active listening and persuasion
skills
  
 
	    
  
 
	Areas
of Responsibility
  
 
	1.New Business Development
  
 
	Incumbent
must close new business with new and existing customers by carrying out the
following:
  
 
	Obtain
leads for new business through channels such as counter referrals, drivers,
Inside Sales, “finder’s keepers”, chamber of commerce business lists, and the
local newspaper
  
 
	Gather
information about customers' business products and process, and their
transportation challenges through face-to-face contact
  
 
	Seek
and identify opportunities to grow the business with existing customers
  
 
	Identify
customer’s needs and develop value propositions to meet those needs
  
 
	Create
a market based pricing structure
  
 
	Prepare
a sales proposal to target the needs of customers
  
 
	Deliver
sales presentation to persuade potential customers to use FedEx products and/or
services
  
 
	2.Account
Servicing
  
 
	Incumbent
must support existing customers with effective customer education by carrying
out the following:
  
 
	Coordinate
with internal resources to teach customers how to use FedEx tools and services
  
 
	Answer
customer questions about FedEx products or services during sales call
  
 
	Create
and execute implementation plans with the customers
  
 
	Monitor
implementation progress to ensure timelines are met
  
 
	Identify
barriers to successful implementation and recommend ways to remove or minimize
them
  
 
	Troubleshoot
and resolve customer’s problems
  
 
	Contact
customers to find out how well the solutions are meeting their business needs
  
 
	Present
review findings to customers using the available system reporting tool
  
 
	In
addition to the above, Senior Account Executive – Field Sales will also need
to:
  
 
	Coach
and guide new team member on sales processes and standards
  
 
	Support
sales trainers, as necessary
  
 
	Assume
lead role for projects as assigned by management
  
 
	Work location: China Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen, Suzhou,
Kunshan, Nantong, Hangzhou, Ningbo, Chongqing, Zhengzhou
